          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "إِنَّ رَسُولَ اَللَّهِ صَلَّى اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "آلِهِ مَشَى خَلْفَ جَنَازَةِ رَجُلٍ مِنَ اَلْأَنْصَارِ فَقِيلَ لَهُ أَ لاَ تَرْكَبُ يَا رَسُولَ اَللَّهِ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " فَقَالَ"
          }
        ]
      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:28:31",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/28/588",
      "text": [
        " «إِنِّي لَأَكْرَهُ أَنْ أَرْكَبَ وَ اَلْمَلاَئِكَةُ يَمْشُونَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.588 - The Messenger of Allah (sw) walked behind the funeral procession of a man from the Ansar.\nHe was asked: \"O’ Messenger of Allah (sw), would you not ride?\"\nHe (sw) replied: \"I dislike riding while the angels are walking.\""
        ]
      }
    },
